      "rationale": "The compression-bending test operates predominantly in the elastic regime for stiffness and yield force QoIs. Literature supports linear elastic titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) properties. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) between screw and rod was informed by prior tribology studies. Sensitivity analysis confirmed QoI insensitivity to mu variations of ±0.1."
